--- TASK SPEC (14) FULL TEXT ---
# 14 — Server: log ingest, pagination, delete, retention purge
**Status:** pending → complete
**Dependencies:** 11, 05
Objective: Central log store in Postgres: workers POST batches; GET paginated; DELETE; retention purge except retain_forever.
In scope: POST worker logs batch; GET /sessions/:id/logs cursor + job_id, level, last; DELETE optional job_id; scheduled purge default 7 days; honor session/job retain_forever.
Out of scope: SSE (15); dual-write files on server phased — document.
Acceptance: integration tests ingest → list → delete; purge removes old, preserves retained.
Testing: cargo test + time-mocked purge.

--- REPOSITORY STATE DISCOVERED ---
- Existing `logs` table (initial migration): id, session_id, job_id, line_seq, stream, content, ingested_at — lacked API fields level/source/worker_id/occurred_at.
- No routes for /sessions/:id/logs or /workers/tasks/:id/logs.
- ServerConfig had log_retention_days_default default 30 in code — task requires 7.

--- NEW MIGRATION (append-only) ---
File: crates/server/migrations/20250320160000_logs_api_fields.sql
- ADD log_level TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'info'
- ADD log_source TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'worker'
- ADD worker_id TEXT REFERENCES workers(id) ON DELETE SET NULL
- ADD occurred_at TIMESTAMPTZ — backfill from ingested_at, NOT NULL, DEFAULT now()
- INDEX logs_session_occurred_id_idx ON (session_id, occurred_at ASC, id ASC)
- INDEX logs_occurred_at_idx ON (occurred_at)

--- API TYPES ---
File: crates/api-types/src/logs.rs
- LogEntry { id, timestamp: DateTime<Utc>, level, session_id, job_id?, worker_id?, source, message }
- WorkerLogIngestItem { timestamp: String, level, message, source }
- WorkerLogsAcceptedResponse { accepted: bool }
- PaginatedLogEntries = Paginated<LogEntry>
crates/api-types/src/lib.rs: mod logs; pub use logs::*

--- SERVER MODULE crates/server/src/logs.rs (behavior summary) ---
- list_session_logs: 404 if session missing; optional job_id UUID, level (case-insensitive via LOWER), last=N (1..500) returns N newest then sorted ascending chronologically, next_cursor always None for last mode; else cursor pagination ascending on (occurred_at, id) with opaque base64 cursor rfc3339|bigint id; limit 1..100 default 20.
- delete_session_logs: optional job_id — if set validates job belongs to session else 404; DELETE scoped rows; else delete all logs for session.
- post_worker_task_logs: job must exist with status='assigned'; FOR UPDATE; max line_seq per session; inserts content as message body, stream fixed 'stdout'; worker_id from job row; parses RFC3339 timestamps.
- run_log_retention_purge(pool, retention_days): DELETE logs WHERE occurred_at < now() - N days AND session.retain_forever=false AND (job_id IS NULL OR job.retain_forever=false); uses days.max(1) internally.

--- ROUTER (crates/server/src/lib.rs) ---
- mod logs; pub use logs::run_log_retention_purge;
- GET+DELETE /sessions/{id}/logs
- POST /workers/tasks/{id}/logs
(all behind API key middleware)

--- MAIN PURGE LOOP (crates/server/src/main.rs) ---
- If db Some(pool): tokio::spawn interval Duration::from_secs(config.log_purge_interval_secs.max(60)); run_log_retention_purge(&pool, config.log_retention_days_default); log stderr on rows removed or error.

